The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Gujarat Gas Company Ltd has posted a 72.25 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 27.32 crore for the first quarter ended March 31, 2005 compared with Rs 15.86 crore in the corresponding quarter in 2003-04. Total income has gone up 14.91 per cent to Rs 160.06 crore for the first quarter from Rs 139.29 crore in the year-ago period, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. Consolidated profit of the group is Rs 33.45 crore for the quarter ended March 31, 2005 compared with Rs 17.73 crore for the same quarter in the previous fiscal. Total income has increased to Rs 194.64 crore for the first quarter from Rs 171.28 crore in same quarter in 2003-04, it said.

 Holcim, a global cement major, has decided to consolidate its data centre operations for the entire Asia-Pacific region with NIIT Technologies. Till recently, NIIT Technologies was operating a dedicated data centre for Holcims business-critical IT applications in Thailand. As part of this engagement, NIIT Technologies will use its data centre and disaster recovery centre in Bangkok to help the Holcim group companies in Asia-Pacific access SAP applications and services round-the-clock, a release said.

 Gulf Oil Corporation Ltd will acquire a 51 per cent stake in Gulf Oil Yantai (Co) Ltd in China for $5 million as part of company?s expansion plans in the Asia-Pacific region. The board today approved the acquisition of stake in the Chinese company, which was wholly owned by Gulf Oil International at a cost of $5 million, executive director V. Ramesh said. The capital infusion would be used to build up a manufacturing facility at Yantai in Shandong province in China with a capacity of 30,000 MT per annum, he said.

 Siemens has bagged an order worth Rs 147.5 crore from Power Grid Corporation of India Ltd (PGCIL) for a turnkey transmission substation project at Seoni in Madhya Pradesh. Siemens Ltd?s power transmission amp; distribution (PTD) division will provide a 765-KV circuit-breaker. 

 Glenmark Pharmacueticals has launch a new division ? Milieus ? to deliver generic products to general practitioners. The products will include inter-infective, cough, cold, allergic, and anti-inflammatory and gastroenterology therapy areas.

 IndusInd Bank Ltd has mobilised Rs 170 crore in its Tier-II bond issue during March. The issue is listed on the wholesale debt market (WDM) segment of the National Stock Exchange (NSE) and is rated by ICRA (LA+) and Fitch [A+ (ind)].

 Priya Biscuits has launched butter enriched coconut cookies. This premium variety is available in coloured polypacks of 200 gms. 

